## Evidence audit

| Predicate | Evidence | Status |
| --- | --- | --- |
| late T5N ACK is not native proof | attribution classification bridge_catchup_after_native_window | green |
| stale Theo/Maya queue was cleared before retest | pending_count: 0 before T5O probe | green |
| native app probe after queue cleanup claimed trigger in window | T5O final_claimed_at null during 45s window | red |
| native app logs show trigger poller activity | T5O log_match_counts all 0 | red |
| bridge catches up after native window | T5O attribution classification bridge_catchup_after_native_window | green as mitigation, not native completion |

## Verdict

Clearing stale pending Theo/Maya triggers did not repair native Pentagon app
handoff activation. The fresh T5O trigger remained unclaimed during a clean
45-second native-only window, then the restored bridge claimed/completed it and
sent the ACK. Native Pentagon handoff activation remains red.
